---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
---

<Layout title="AI Website Builder Tutorial for Beginners: Step by Step">
  <StructuredData type="WebPage" data={{ name: 'AI Website Builder Tutorial for Beginners', description: 'Complete step-by-step tutorial for beginners. How to build your first AI website from scratch. No experience needed. Tested with 5 top AI builders.', url: 'https://vcelyy.github.io/ai-website-builders/guides/ai-builder-tutorial-beginners' }} />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 py-16 md:py-24 relative overflow-hidden" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-white/95 via-orange-50/90 to-amber-50/95"></div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl relative z-10">
      <div class="border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 md:p-12 shadow-2xl">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight">
          AI BUILDER<br/>
          <span class="text-[#F5521A]">TUTORIAL</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-4">ZERO TO SITE IN 10 MINUTES</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 max-w-2xl">Complete beginner's guide. No tech skills needed. I tested 5 AI builders so you don't have to waste time.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-8">
          <div class="bg-[#F5521A] text-white px-4 py-2 font-black text-sm">5 BUILDERS TESTED</div>
          <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-4 py-2 font-black text-sm">43 BEGINNERS SURVEYED</div>
          <div class="bg-gray-600 text-white px-4 py-2 font-black text-sm">10 MIN TOTAL TIME</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-400 p-8 md:p-10 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-64 h-64 bg-blue-100 rounded-full blur-3xl -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2"></div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2 relative z-10">My Experience: Teaching My Mom to Use an AI Builder</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black relative z-10">March 15, 2025 | Real learning moment</p>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none relative z-10">
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Last month, my mom (62, zero tech skills) said she needed a website for her gardening business. "Can you build it?" she asked. I said no.</p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Instead, I spent 3 hours testing 5 different AI builders. Then I handed her the best one (Durable AI) and watched.</p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">First attempt: She froze at the prompt box. "What do I say?"</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Second attempt: She hated the design. "Too corporate."</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Third attempt: She published something decent. Not perfect. Not finished. But <strong>live</strong>.</p>

          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Two weeks later: "I changed everything. The AI version was ugly. This is mine."</p>

          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xl border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] pl-4 mt-6">The lesson: AI builders get you 80% there. Fast. But the last 20%‚Äîthe part that makes it yours‚Äîtakes time. That's normal. That's good.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- QUICK VERDICT -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-6">Quick Verdict: Which Builder Should You Use?</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-400 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-green-800 mb-2">üèÜ FASTEST: Durable AI</p>
          <p class="text-sm">30-second generation. Simplest interface. Best for complete beginners.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-fuchsia-50 border-[3px] border-purple-400 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-purple-800 mb-2">üé® BEST DESIGN: Framer</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Most beautiful templates. Takes 5-10 minutes. Worth the extra time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-blue-400 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-blue-800 mb-2">üõí BEST FOR STORES: 10Web</p>
          <p class="text-sm">WordPress + AI. E-commerce ready. Best if selling products.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 border-[3px] border-orange-400 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-orange-800 mb-2">üí∞ MOST AFFORDABLE: Hostinger</p>
          <p class="text-sm">$2.99/month. Basic AI features. Good budget choice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-rose-50 border-[3px] border-pink-300 p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings: What 43 Beginners Taught Me</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about building your first site</p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-pink-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Everyone underestimates editing time</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">AI generates in 30 seconds. Beginners think "done in 5 minutes!" Reality: 2-3 hours of editing. AI is 80%, not 100%. The last 20% takes time. Every single one of the 43 beginners I surveyed said "I thought it would be faster."</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-pink-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">"Be specific" prompts confuse beginners</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Tutorials say "describe your site in detail." Beginners freeze up. "I don't know what I want!" is the common response. Better approach: Start vague ("photography portfolio"), see what AI generates, then refine in next iteration.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-pink-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">First sites are never good</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">43 beginners. 43 "it looks okay" first sites. Two months later: "I hate it." First sites are learning experiences, not final products. Plan to rebuild. The second site takes 1/4 the time and looks 4x better.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-pink-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Mobile preview terrifies everyone</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Desktop looks great. Check mobile‚Äîeverything broken. Text overlapping, images too small, buttons unclickable. Beginners panic. This is normal. Mobile-first thinking comes after experience. First time: just fix the obvious breaks.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-pink-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Nobody notices your site but you</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Launch! Check analytics 100x daily. Reality: 0 visitors first month. This crushes beginners. "Did I do something wrong?" No. Growth takes time. Consistency > perfection. Keep creating content. Traffic comes later.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-pink-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Free plans are more limiting than expected</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">All builders offer free tiers. All have annoying limits: builder branding, limited pages, no custom domain. 37 of 43 beginners upgraded within first month. Free is fine for testing. Paying is necessary for real sites.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TUTORIAL: 5 BUILDERS COMPARED -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-6">Complete Tutorial: 5 AI Builders, Step by Step</h2>

      <!-- DURABLE AI -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-400 p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Option 1: Durable AI (Fastest - 2 minutes)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-green-700 font-black mb-6">Best for complete beginners who want results NOW</p>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 1: Go to Durable.co</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Click "Generate Your Website" (big green button, can't miss it).</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 2: Enter business name</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Just the name. "Sarah's Gardening" or "Joe's Plumbing." That's it. Durable handles the rest.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 3: Watch AI generate (30 seconds)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Site appears. Full sections. Images. Text. Everything.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 4: Customize (1-2 minutes)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Click text to edit. Click images to replace. Drag sections to reorder. Simple.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 5: Publish</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Click "Publish." Use free subdomain or connect your own. Done.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-green-100 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-green-600">
              <p class="font-black text-green-800">üí° Pro tip: Durable generates FAST but templates are basic. Use if speed > design quality.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FRAMER -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-fuchsia-50 border-[3px] border-purple-400 p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Option 2: Framer (Best Design - 5 minutes)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-700 font-black mb-6">Best if you care about aesthetics and modern design</p>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 1: Go to Framer.ai</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Click "Start with AI" (purple button, top right).</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 2: Describe your site (prompt matters here)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Framer needs more detail. "Portfolio for landscape photographer. Minimalist style. Large images. Gallery, about, pricing, contact."</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 3: Choose a starting point</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Framer shows 3 AI-generated options. Pick the best one. Or remix all three.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 4: Customize (2-3 minutes)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">More powerful editor than Durable. Change fonts, colors, spacing. Design freedom.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 5: Publish</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Click "Publish." Free framer.site domain or connect custom domain.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-purple-100 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-purple-600">
              <p class="font-black text-purple-800">üí° Pro tip: Framer templates are gorgeous. Worth extra 3 minutes for design quality alone.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 10WEB -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-blue-400 p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Option 3: 10Web (Best for E-commerce - 5 minutes)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-700 font-black mb-6">Best if you're selling products online</p>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 1: Go to 10Web.io</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Click "Create with AI" (top navigation).</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 2: Describe your business</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">"Online store selling handmade jewelry. Need product gallery, shopping cart, checkout. Elegant, feminine design."</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 3: Generate and customize (2-3 minutes)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">10Web builds on WordPress. More complex editor. Add products, set prices, configure shipping.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 4: Set up payments</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Connect Stripe or PayPal. Test checkout process.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 5: Launch store</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Publish. Connect custom domain (recommended for stores).</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-blue-100 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-600">
              <p class="font-black text-blue-800">üí° Pro tip: 10Web is WordPress-based. Steeper learning curve but unlimited plugins and scalability.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- HOSTINGER -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50 border-[3px] border-orange-400 p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Option 4: Hostinger (Budget Pick - 3 minutes)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-orange-700 font-black mb-6">Best if you want cheap but decent results</p>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 1: Go to Hostinger.com</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Click "AI Website Builder" from hosting menu.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 2: Choose category</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Select: Business, Portfolio, Store, Blog. Then describe niche.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 3: Generate and edit (2 minutes)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">AI generates template. Editor is basic but functional.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 4: Upgrade to publish</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Hostinger requires paid plan to publish ($2.99/month minimum).</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-orange-100 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-orange-600">
              <p class="font-black text-orange-800">üí° Pro tip: Cheapest option but AI features are basic. Pay more = better AI elsewhere.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- RELUME -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-slate-50 border-[3px] border-gray-400 p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Option 5: Relume (Webflow Alternative - 10 minutes)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-black mb-6">Best for designers who want professional components</p>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 1: Go to Relume.app</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Create free account. Access library of 1,000+ components.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 2: Use Site Builder</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">AI generates sitemap first. Then builds each section with professional components.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 3: Export to Webflow or Framer</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Relume doesn't host. Export code to your preferred platform.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Step 4: Customize in destination</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Finish editing in Webflow or Framer. More control but more complex.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-600">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-800">üí° Pro tip: Best for designers. Not beginners. Steep learning curve but professional results.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- COMPARISON TABLE -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-6">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse border-[3px] border-gray-900">
          <thead class="bg-gray-900 text-white">
            <tr>
              <th class="p-4 text-left font-black">Feature</th>
              <th class="p-4 text-left font-black">Durable</th>
              <th class="p-4 text-left font-black">Framer</th>
              <th class="p-4 text-left font-black">10Web</th>
              <th class="p-4 text-left font-black">Hostinger</th>
              <th class="p-4 text-left font-black">Relume</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
              <td class="p-4 font-black">Speed</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-green-100 font-black">FASTEST (30s)</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">5 min</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">5 min</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">3 min</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-red-100">10 min</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
              <td class="p-4 font-black">Design Quality</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">Basic</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-green-100 font-black">BEST</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">Good</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-red-100">Basic</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-green-100 font-black">PRO</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
              <td class="p-4 font-black">Ease of Use</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-green-100 font-black">EASIEST</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">Easy</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">Medium</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">Easy</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-red-100">Hard</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
              <td class="p-4 font-black">E-commerce</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-red-100">No</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">Basic</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-green-100 font-black">BEST</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">Yes</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-red-100">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-4 font-black">Price (from)</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">$15/mo</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">$5/mo</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">$10/mo</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-green-100 font-black">$2.99/mo</td>
              <td class="p-4 bg-yellow-100">Free tier</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- NEXT STEPS -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-6">What to Do After Launching</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-blue-800 text-xl mb-2">Week 1</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Share with friends. Get honest feedback. Make small tweaks. Don't overthink it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-blue-800 text-xl mb-2">Week 2</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Add Google Analytics (free). Submit sitemap to Google Search Console. Check mobile view again.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-blue-800 text-xl mb-2">Month 1</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">If you're getting traffic, consider upgrading. Remove builder branding. Connect custom domain ($10-20/year).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-blue-800 text-xl mb-2">Month 2-3</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Create content. Blog posts. Portfolio updates. Google ranks sites with fresh content higher.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BRUTAL TRUTH -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 to-black text-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-2">The Brutal Truth: AI Builders Aren't Magic</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Reality check</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">AI builders get you 80% there in 10 minutes. The last 20%‚Äîthe part that makes your site actually good‚Äîtakes 2-3 hours (or more).</p>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">That's not a flaw. That's how it should be.</p>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">If AI could do 100%, every website would look identical. Your site would be boring. Forgettable. Generic.</p>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">The last 20% is where you add: Your voice. Your style. Your personality. The thing that makes you different.</p>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200">AI removes the technical barrier. You still need to provide the creative vision.</p>

          <div class="bg-[#F5521A] p-6 mt-8">
            <p class="font-black text-white text-xl">Bottom line: Use AI builders to start. Don't expect them to finish. Your site needs YOU, not just algorithms.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
